Red Velvet is a popular South Korean girl group that was formed by SM Entertainment. The group made their debut on August 1, 2014, with the single "Happiness". The original lineup of the group consisted of five members: Irene, Seulgi, Wendy, Joy, and Yeri. Since their debut, Red Velvet has become one of the most successful and influential K-pop girl groups of all time, known for their unique and diverse musical style, powerful vocals, and dynamic performances. They have released multiple hit singles and albums, won numerous awards, and have a large and dedicated fanbase both in Korea and around the world.